From: TurboQuant CANN Port
Date: Sat May 16 2026
Subject: [PATCH] ggml-cann: add TQ3_4S/TQ3_1S quantized matmul support

Add TQ3 weight dequant → FP16 matmul path for the CANN backend.

The CANN backend's ggml_cann_mul_mat previously only supported
F32/F16/BF16/Q4_0/Q8_0. This adds TQ3_4S (type 46) and TQ3_1S (type 44).

Strategy: CPU-dequant TQ3 blocks to FP32 → ACL cast to FP16 on device →
ACL BatchMatMul. This is a correct but slow path; future work should
replace CPU dequant with an Ascend C kernel.

Dequant helpers are consolidated in tq3_cann_kernels.h to avoid code
duplication between the CANN backend and test files.

